  <section class="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Monthly or Annual</aside>
    <article>
      Codio aims to support the developer community as deeply as possible - we’ll always
      have a free option and provide preferential pricing for schools and education users.
      With professionals, we’ll reward you for making an annual commitment.
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Enterprise Licenses</aside>
    <article>
      Codio provides enterprise and corporate user licences with a minimum
      of 5 users or more. You can manage all enterprise users at the
      organisation level and vary the number of users throughout the
      licence period.
    </article>
  </section>


  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Stacks & Starter Packs</aside>
    <article>
      <p>
        Codio provides all users with unlimited access
        to a library of coding environments - you’ll find stacks for just
        about any project requirement - and our starter packs take your
        experience to the next level with stacks, starting point sample
        project code, and, in many cases, rich instructions.
      </p>
      <p>
        Enterprise users can access all of Codios stacks and starter
        packs, create custom enterprise stacks and starter packs which are
        ideal for developer on-boarding, transitioning between projects and
        assessing new developer team members. Save man weeks of lost
        productivity.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Private Projects</aside>
    <article>
      Free users wishing to trial Codio with private coding projects can use
      Codio with one private project for one 30 day period. For
      professional users, Codio provides unlimited private projects within
      your allocated disk space.
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Infrastructure & IDE</aside>
    <article>
      Professional subscribers enjoy significantly greater choice of
      infrastructure - with larger RAM and storage.
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <aside>Always-on boxes</aside>
    <article>
      All subscriptions tiers with an allocation of always-on boxes;
      managing which projects run with an always-on box is a simple one
      click choice in the projects dashboard
    </article>
  </section>

